# agent-os — Cline rules
# Same intent as CLAUDE.md. For users of Cline (VS Code extension).

## Brain (AI context)
brain/about-you.md        — who you are, your stack, your goals
brain/active-projects.md  — what's being built right now
brain/coding-standards.md — hard rules for this project
brain/decisions.md        — why things are the way they are
brain/ai-behavior.md      — how every AI in this env should behave

## Critical rule
Architecture, security, and data-model decisions require the dual-review gate.
See docs/03-dual-review-gate.md before implementing anything in those categories.

## Behavior
Follow brain/ai-behavior.md exactly.
Key points:
- Direct and concise. No filler.
- Say immediately if something is wrong.
- Explain what and why when asking for confirmation — not just "run this?".
- No unsolicited refactors or scope creep.
- Flag security issues before anything else.
